  "learn": {
    "heading": "Add, multiply, then halve",
    "intro": "<p>A trapezoid has two parallel sides called <strong>bases</strong>. To find its area you <strong>add the two bases</strong>, <strong>multiply by the height</strong>, then take <strong>half</strong>. Halving is the same as multiplying by 1/2 or dividing by 2.</p>",
    "examples": [
      "<strong>Halving:</strong> half of 10 = 5, half of 14 = 7, half of 20 = 10.",
      "<strong>Adding bases:</strong> if the bases are 6 and 4, then 6 + 4 = <strong>10</strong>. That sum is what you multiply by the height next."
    ]
  },
